article.description: — Dominick Harris scored 28 points and Loyola Marymount held off UNLV 78-75 on Saturday.
article.headline: Harris scores 28 to lead Loyola Marymount over UNLV 78-75
article.linkText: Harris scores 28 to lead Loyola Marymount over UNLV 78-75
article.story: HENDERSON, Nev. -- — Dominick Harris scored 28 points and Loyola Marymount held off UNLV 78-75 on Saturday. Harris also contributed five rebounds for the Lions (6-4). Alex Merkviladze scored 15 points with nine rebounds and made two free throws with 1 second left. Lars Thiemann shot 4 of 9 from the field and 5 for 7 from the line to finish with 13 points. Dedan Thomas Jr. finished with 17 points and eight assists for the Rebels (3-4). UNLV also got 15 points, two steals and five blocks from Kalib Boone. Isaiah Cottrell also had 14 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
